<br>
AC is king if you are a warrior.  I will debate that issue for SK.  It is extremely important but I would not say it is must before all else.  We are the aggro management professionals.  We are designed with inferior AC to warriors.  Our AC is enough to tank when your main tank cannot.  I would not be as good a main tank as a troll, but I am good enough.<br>
<br>
I point that out because you are now seeing what distinguishes the troll/ogre sk from a de/eru sk.  We can get good strength more easily than they can find intelligence.  When it comes time to cast darkness/fear for fear kiting in maidens, you need enough mana to do that more than one or two cycles due to the extreme hitpoints of the critters.  Your straight melee stats of AC/stam can't help you here.  Nobody can simply straight up tank these high level critters.  Yes, the ogres/trolls have the tank stats but I frankly think those are not as significant as the ability to cast and taunt.  We are after all the aggro management professionals.  We simply take the aggro when we want/need it and that is what makes for win/lose on battles.<br>
<br>
In addition, if you need to pull taunt off the casters in Velks or elsewhere, you need the mana to cast heart flutter, shroud pain, vortex to get their attention.  The taunt button is not enough alone and your damage output via melee is usually not enough either.  Trolls/ogres can do that a few times but if you get a large pull or simply have an aggresive pulling team, your batteries will dry up way too soon to be able to keep the job up.  I always have a bar or two left after long pull series and its the casters calling for med break.<br>
<br>
Now that is all nice info but, it comes down to what you like to see on the screen.  Each race will provide you with advantages and challenges.  All of use by level 50 will have figured those out and play our version of the SK.  <br>
