<a href="http://www.houseavendur.com"> House Avendur </a><BR> </a> -A Shadow Knights obsession with death not only borders on insanity, it wallows in it-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umartonbloodfang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marton Bloodfang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/15/02 3:05:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshadowknight.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pick an ogre</span><hr size=1> Will jump in here as I always enjoyed the &quot;dark&quot; side of EQ, RP wise anyway.<br>
<br>
In the endagme, stats are rather irrelevant as with a raid, your melee stats will be buffed close, if not, to max, and you'll have a sizable amount of HPS from Focus/RH/Aego.  Looks are important and, quite possibly, the definitive reason to pick a race, however as aforementioned, never overlook the nice li'l RP opportuinties each race provides...<br>
<br>
Troll/Ogre - We've all read stories about what lurks in the deepest jungles and darkest swamps.  These guys are the &quot;monsters&quot; that will attack anything and, pretty much, eat it.  Whereas they have some form of primitive &quot;society&quot;, much of their instincts are animal and they'd be happy to kill you and eat you or die trying.  Matter of factly, its both a boon and a disadvantage for these races.  They would attempt to overcome you with force, however, wouldn't know a losing battle until they were one foot out of the grave.  Shadowknights in these situations are most likely revered due to their &quot;more than the average&quot; fighter traits.  <br>
<br>
Iksar - Xenophobic race, and probably would never be seen outside of Kunark.  After decades of bondage to the Shissar, they, as of Kunark's release, are just entering a Renaissaince for their society.  A proud race, they basically care for one thing - survival and preservation.  They worship &quot;fear&quot; for two main reasons - its the portfolio of their creator, and also its befits their nature after being enslaved for so long.  Most likely, if encountered, Iksar would not hastily attack (unless its a known enemy such as the Sarnak, Kunark Giants, Goblins, Drolvarg, Shissar), but rather approach with much caution and trepidation.  They're an intelligent race, hoping to reclaim their former glory via a cultural rebirth, however, most truthfuly they just want to live in relative isolation surrounded by an environment they control.  <br>
<br>
Dark Elves - Argolic said evil by choice, I disagree.  Dark Elves know nothing else of how to present themselves other than the way their society teaches.  Read any D&amp;D Drow reference and you'll see all facets of Dark Elven EQ society...can't trust anyone, everyone is a potential enemy.  Their hatred for the WE and HE is one of envy (as states their creation story), and its their inflated pride which eggs them to want to conquer all Norrath.  Calculated killers, they are, and certainly the perfect antithesis to any &quot;good&quot; race/class, however too narrow for my tastes.<br>
<br>
Now the good stuff...<br>
<br>
Erudites - Seekers of the Dark Truth (does anyone know what the &quot;Dark Truth&quot; is?).  As the despcription states, you seek answers to this [Dark Truth] in the dimming eyes of your enemies.  The death of others is a means to an elaborate equation that you are attempting to uncover.  At the root, Erudites are scholars, maybe more in the vein of Dr. Frankenstein and Dr. Mordenheim (sp?) from AD&amp;D's Ravenloft.  Within death lies many unanswered questions, and you are seeking the answers in a most violent, yet calculated way.<br>
<br>
I do not see why they were given Cazic as their deity, maybe as they were routed from Erudin and forced to live in Toxxulia as outcasts and the fear of repercussions from such study would lead to worship of the Lord of Fear, however, it was always fun to play the role of the intellectual Cazicite.  Giving the appropriation of fear a more sinister twist.  In contrast, however, books in Paineel do mention Bertoxxulous as the lead deity of Paineelians, dunno what's going on there, maybe a typo. /shrug<br>
<br>
Humans - <br>
<br>
Of Innoruuk - ugh, leave these guys for the twinks.  You want to start close to all the trade and easiest exp for low levels, play a Human SK of Inny.  Yeah, they want to control the FP Militia like the Inkies manipulate the Ogres/Trolls, other than that, I have no clue.  They, of all, to me are the most ignorant SKs around..why?  Because if they believe that with Innoruuk's coming the human population of his worship will be spared, they have another thing coming.  /yawn<br>
<br>
Of Bertoxxulous - These guys are the shiz.  The Bloodsabres are the ones that will kidnap your sleeping children from their snug li'l beds, drag them down into the sewers and sacrifice them in some dark ritual.  Think extreme cultists when you consider Bloodsabres.  You know, the ones laughing maniacally to themselves in the shadows of some Qeynos streetcorner.  Bloodsabres would make for an interesting RP as they are patient in their methodology.  The end of Norrath will come, and at the hands of Bertoxxulous, however, the plague and disease the wish to spread takes time to reach full potential.  Till then, they'll sit in their sewers, plot against Antonius Bayle III, perform their sick rituals, and await the coming of the Plaguebringer...the Shadowknights, however will actively promote the decay of Norrath, by venturing forth and providing a slow death to any whom they meet...and enjoy it.<br>
<br>
